racingFormOutcome.overview: Finally off the mark at 12th attempt when making all upped to 1m6f in cheekpieces at Musselburgh in August (left Mark Johnston for 16,5000GBP since then); that was off much-reduced mark, is only 2lb higher on return for new yard and should have more to offer reinvented as a stayer; major player again and has form on Polytrack.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: excelled over 6f-1m at 2-3, won Phoenix S, & Irish 2,000 Gns; very good sire, inc The Grey Gatsby
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E50,000 Y, Â£16,500 Don Sept 16; sixth living foal; half-brother to French winners Taverny (9.7f-1m4f; RPR 94), Transparence (1m4f; 80) and Trappeur (10.5f; 80) and Qatar 5/5f-6f winner Trompettiste; dam French 12.5f winner (inc Group 2; 111)

racingFormOutcome.overview: Well held at big prices in three 1m2f maidens during the summer, but looked a different proposition upped to 2m on handicap debut when going close behind emphatic subsequent winner at Lingfield (AW) in September; 3lb higher here but open to more progress and is a leading contender.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class sprinter, excellent sire, can get fast, high-class 2yos, progeny often progress well
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 140,000gns Y; second foal; half-brother to 1m 2yo winner Moontime (RPR 89); dam 9.6f-1m4f winner (inc Group 2; 111), half-sister to dam of Cursory Glance out of Musidora winning granddaughter of top-class middle-distance performer Time Charter

racingFormOutcome.overview: Minor form in two starts at up to 1m4f for Andre Fabre in France in the spring; well beaten for new yard at Salisbury and no impact when 66-1 on handicap debut here (1m4f) last month; needs to raise game and some doubt whether this switch to 2m will suit on pedigree.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: outstanding 1m-10f dirt winner at 3-5, winner of Travers; sire of Rachel Alexandra & Plum Pretty
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Â£21,000 Asc May 16; 3rd foal; brother to US 7.5f-8.5f winner Dickinson, half-brother to US 5.5f/6f winner Telegraph Hill; dam US 8.5f Grade 1 winner (RPR 115), out of Listed-placed daughter of Italian 1m2f Group 1 winner Flagbird from family of Mineshaft

racingFormOutcome.overview: Ten-race maiden who has not really progressed; fair fourth in 2m handicap at Chelmsford three weeks ago but needs to settle better and raise form a few notches to be a big factor here; others more persuasive.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: won Dewhurst and Derby, 2nd in 2,000 Guineas, by Mark Of Esteem; gets 2yos, progeny progress
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 13,500gns F, E17,000 Y; third foal; half-brother to winners Al (1m4f; RPR 87) and Impertinent (1m4f AW; 53); dam 1m2f winner (70), half-sister to high-class 7f-1m1f winner Norse Dancer (stayed 1m4f) out of 1m2f winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Regressive form in three starts, latest when tailed off in Chelmsford claimer (1m) on recent return for new yard; quite a lot to prove but is a half-sister to two fairly useful 1m4f-1m6f winners and could show much more now switched to a staying trip on handicap debut; worth checking in market.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top 1m-10f winner at 3-4, smart 7f winner at 2, out of decent miler; fair start with early crops
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 2,500gns Nkt July 2016; 3rd foal; half-sister to 1m4f-1m6f winners The Cashel Man (RPR 94) and Thunder Pass (88); dam 1m4f winner (86). half-sister to 7.4f Group 3 winner Hamairi and to dam of 1m4f Group 1 winner Seal Of Appoval, out of 1m winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Runner-up off 3lb higher at Salisbury (1m) in June but laboured in middle-distance handicaps in both subsequent starts, latest for new yard in September; plenty to prove again now upped to this trip and is 0-7.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: 7f winner at 2, later top-class 1m-10f performer, family of Nureyev; sire of Madame Chiang
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 8,000gns Nkt July 16; 7th foal; half-sister to winners Bowdler's Magic (8.6f-2m inc AW/2yo; RPR 97), Luz De La Luna (1m AW 2yo; 87), and Always Eager (9.4f AW; 66); dam Argentinian 1m Gr 1 winner, granddaughter of Californian Oaks winner Whydidju.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Big prices and well beaten in three maidens, latest when 13l seventh over 1m4f here last month; now switches to a minor handicap but improvement is needed and not sure step up to this trip will suit.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unbeaten G1 winner over 7f at 2, unraced at 3+ due to injury, sire of Trading Leather, Pleascach
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 315,000 Y; second foal; half-brother to 1m 2yo winner Encore L'Amour (stays 1m2f; RPR 100); dam 1m2f winner (72), sister to US 1m1f/1m2f Grade 1 winner Ticker Tape, half-sister to 6f-1m winner Sant Elena (dam of Reckless Abandon)

racingFormOutcome.overview: Sole win from 21 starts was in a 6f nursery here last September; numerous decent efforts this year but not at best on last three starts and took strong hold over 1m4f here last Wednesday; stamina under pressure now upped to this trip and probably best to look elsewhere.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: useful multiple 7-8f winner at 2-4 in France, from excellent family; good strike rate with 2yos
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Fourth foal; sister to 7f-1m winner Multi Bene (RPR 100) and 5f-7f AW winner Multitask (inc at 2; 84); dam unraced half-sister to Listed-placed 1m2f winner Bana Wu out of half-sister to good 2yo Strategic Prince

racingFormOutcome.overview: Got much closer to the target upped to 13.5f on handicap debut when keeping-on 4l fourth of 13 at Chelmsford (first-time visor) last month; still unexposed and interesting if he can build on that now tackling 2m.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 10-12f winner at 3 in US, unraced at 2, family of Rubiano & Tapit; first foals 2012
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: $50,000 F, E200,000 Y; 8th living foal; half-brother to five winners notably Polytechnicien (French 1m2f Group 3; RPR 115); dam placed 6f-1m in France, half-sister to US Grade 1 winners Dare And Go (1m2f) and Go Deputy (1m4f)

racingFormOutcome.overview: Half-sister to 7f 2yo/useful 2m hurdle winner Tea In Transvaal (RPR 80) and 5f 2yo winner Nelspruit (87); dam Group-placed French 5.5f 2yo winner; doubts on pedigree about starting off at 1m; tough debut.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: useful 1m 2yo, smart over 10f at 3-5; good source of classy, tough horses inc 2yos from summer
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Fourth foal; half-sister to 7f 2yo/useful 2m hurdle winner Tea In Transvaal (RPR 80) and 5f 2yo winner Nelspruit (87); dam Group-placed French 5.5f 2yo winner (stayed 7f; 95), out of French 7.5f winning daughter of US 1m1f and 1m2f Grade 1 winner Reloy

racingFormOutcome.overview: Half-sister to 1m-1m4f winner Golden Horn (including at two; Derby/Arc) and 1m2f Listed winner Eastern Belle (106); dam unraced half-sister to Coronation Stakes winner Rebecca Sharp; pedigree to die for and market will reveal what she's been showing at home.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class multiple winning sprinter at 2 & 4, excellent source of precocious and speedy 2yos
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Fourth foal; half-sister to 1m-1m4f winner Golden Horn (inc at 2; Derby/Arc; 132) and 1m2f Listed winner Eastern Belle (106); dam unraced half-sister to Coronation Stakes winner Rebecca Sharp and 11.4f Group 3 winner Mystic Knight

racingFormOutcome.overview: 25-1, never involved when beaten about 6l at Haydock (1m; hood on, retained); can learn from that but bred to want further.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 7f winner at 2, top miler at 3 (won QEII), by Dubawi; good start with first 2yos
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: (40,000gns vendor Y); 4th foal; half-sister to winners Forced Family Fun (1m2f-1m5f Flat; RPR 87/2m hurdle) and Kifaaya (1m2f 2yo; 74); dam 7.4f (at 2) to 2m2f winner (inc Northumberland Plate; 104) sister to Italian 1,000 Guineas winner Golden Nepi

racingFormOutcome.overview: Dam placed 7f (at two) and 1m2f (RPR 80), half-sister to 1m Listed winner Dolores (dam of good stayers Duncan, Samuel and Gretchen); trainer's newcomers often improve for a run but they can win first time, as one did here last month.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unbeaten G1 winner over 7f at 2, unraced at 3+ due to injury, sire of Trading Leather, Pleascach
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Second foal; dam placed 7f (at 2) and 1m2f (RPR 80), half-sister to 1m Listed winner Dolores (dam of good stayers Duncan, Samuel and Gretchen), out of Belgian 7f (at 2) and 1m1f winning half-sister to French 1m Gr 3 winner Wavy Run

racingFormOutcome.overview: 500,000gns yearling; siblings include winners Field Of Miracles (1m4f AW/Ribblesdale second; RPR 110) and Cameron Highland (1m1f-11.6f; 111); dam US 1m 2yo winner, sister to Grade 1 1m1f/1m2f winner Arravale; yard 16-83 with 2yos here in last five years, but their debut is often needed.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 12f colt, top pedigree; brilliant sire of 2yos, plus progeny progress well, multiple champ
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 500,000gns Y; 7th foal; sister to winners Field Of Miracles (1m4f AW/Ribblesdale second; RPR 110) & Cameron Highland (1m1f-11.6f; 111), half-sister to 2 more inc Sour Mash (1m2f-1m3f, 95); dam US 1m 2yo winner, sister to Grade 1 1m1f/1m2f winner Arravale

racingFormOutcome.overview: Out of sister to Milan; lots of promise on 7f debut here, buried in the pack until the straight, when coming with sweeping run into second; form boosted since and major player upped to 1m.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: won Haydock Sprint Cup; a leading sire, excellent record with 2yos but progeny train on well
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: (100,000gns vendor F); second foal; dam 1m4f AW winner (RPR 88), sister to Leger winner Milan, half-sister to 1m4f Group 3 winner Koora out of 1m4f Group 3 winner from family of Derby winner Kahyasi

racingFormOutcome.overview: Out of French Oaks winner; 9-4 for Nottingham debut over 1m but soft ground could have held her back as she was beaten a very long way in fifth; early days to be writing her off but this is a warm race.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 12f colt, top pedigree; brilliant sire of 2yos, plus progeny progress well, multiple champ
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Sixth foal; half-sister four winners inc Fencing (7f 2yo and 1m Listed; RPR 115), Obsidian (1m; 91)and Signed Sealed (1m4f Fibresand; 86); dam French/US 1m-1m4f winner (inc at 2/French Oaks; 120), half-sister to French Derby winner Lawman

racingFormOutcome.overview: Dam unraced half-sister to US 1m2f Grade 1 winner Miss Shop and US 6f Grade 2 winner Trappe Shot;  trainer 0-5 with 2yos here but had three individual winners in this age bracket, two of them first time.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unbeaten G1 winner over 7f at 2, unraced at 3+ due to injury, sire of Trading Leather, Pleascach
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam unraced half-sister to US 1m2f Grade 1 winner Miss Shop, US 6f Grade 2 winner Trappe Shot and 6f stakes winenr Shop Again (dam of 8.5f 2yo Grade 1 winner Power Broker), out of half-sister to 7f/1m2f Grade 2 winner Lay Down

racingFormOutcome.overview: 20-1, did well when sixth on her 1m debut at Newbury, considering trainer tends to be very patient with his youngsters; open to improvement but awkwardly placed from this draw.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 2yo, won Prix Morny & Middle Park, high-class 6-7f 3yo; good source of sprinters/milers
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: (25,000gns vendor F); 9th foal, half-sister to five winners inc Nasri (6f-7f inc at 2/AW; 104), Ellmau (6f-1m3f, inc at 2/Fibresand; 100) and Royal Sharp (French 9.5f AW 2yo; 75); dam 1m2f Flat; 81/2m4f hurdle winner, half-sister to dam of Canford Cliffs

racingFormOutcome.overview: Siblings include winners Great Order (1m/1m2f; RPR 108) and Gavroche (US 1m turf/8.5f dirt); dam 1m (at two) to 1m4f (Group 2 Ribblesdale) winner; trainer ending season with a flourish and has very strong strike-rate with 2yos on AW, 23-79 with them here in last five years.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 7-8f US dirt colt, top-class sire, gets smart 2yos, sire of top 2yo filly Cursory Glance
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 4th foal; sister to winners Great Order (1m/1m2f RPR 108) and Gavroche (US 1m turf/8.5f dirt), half-sister to 1m/9.4f AW winner Thatchmaster (90); dam 1m (at 2) to 1m4f (Group 2 Ribblesdale) winner (114), sister to useful 1m2f-1m6f winner Willing Foe

racingFormOutcome.overview: 33-1 and never reached the firing line on C&D debut though she did keep persevering in the straight; open to improvement but asked a lot today.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unraced at 2, later top class over 8-10f, high-class sire inc. Dutch Art & Nannina
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Third foal; half-sister to AW winners Mystikana (1m4f; RPR 72) and Father Stone (7f 2yo; 68); dam 11.4f-1m4f winner (inc AW; 85), half-sister to useful 1m4f-2m winner Mana D'Argent (1m4f-2m) and 1m6f Listed winner Winged D'Argent out of 6f/7f winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: 240,000euros yearling; dam 1m2f-1m4f winner (including Group 3), bred Listed-placed 1m 2yo winner Elas Diamond, 1m2f-2m2f winner Pallasator (including Group 2) and 7f AW 2yo winner Alphonsus (103); yard has respectable record with 2yos here but she'll need to be smart to win this.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class Australian sprinter; prolific source of precocious/smart 2yos, champ sire in Australia
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E240,000 Y; ninth foal; closely related to Listed-placed 1m 2yo winner Elas Diamond (RPR 97), half-sister to 1m2f-2m2f winner Pallasator (inc Group 2; 116); and 7f AW 2yo winner Alphonsus (103); dam 1m2f-1m4f winner (inc Group 3; 118), out of 1m winner

racingFormOutcome.owner: H H Sheikh Mohammed Bin Khalifa Al Thani
racingFormOutcome.overview: Easy to back at 25-1 for Leicester debut (1m) and beaten about 18l in the end, after racing freely; other days for her.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: won Prix du Jockey-Club & Prix Jean Prat; excellent source of 2yos summer onwards, Classic sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 190,000gns Y; first foal; dam 1m-1m2f winner (RPR 74), half-sister to Listed-placed winners This Is The Day (1m2f) and Vanity Day (8.6f AW) out of 1m Listed wining daughter of 1m Group 1 winner Rebecca Sharp

racingFormOutcome.overview: Dam 1m Fibresand 2yo/1m4f Polytrack winner (RPR 86); trainer had few 2yo winners in recent years and none since 2014; up against it.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart 7f 2yo, later top 10-12f performer; gets 2yo winners from summer onwards, progeny progress
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam 1m Fibresand 2yo/1m4f Polytrack winner (RPR 86), half-sister to  winners inc Captain Cullen (fairly useful 5f-1m) and Dee Cee Elle (9.4f-1m4f//2m & 2m3f hurdle) out of 1m7f winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Sister to three winners, notably Cannock Chase (Grade 1, RPR 120); represents top connections (who won both divisions of this maiden with newcomers last year) and of obvious interest on paper.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 2yo/Belmont Stakes winner, capable of siring smart 2yos but progeny progress well
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Sixth foal; sister to three winners inc Cannock Chase (1m2f-1m4f, inc Canadian Grade 1; RPR 120) and Pisco Sour (1m-1m2f inc Group 2; 114) dam fourth over 1m2f in France, half-sister to 7f-8.8f (inc Group 2) winner Lord Admiral

racingFormOutcome.overview: 100-1 and well held in Newbury maiden 12 days ago; similar fate beckons here.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: Beresford Stakes & Racing Post Trophy winner as 2yo, 1m 2f Group 3 winning 3yo, first 2yos 2016
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E7,000 Y; 7th foal; half sister to 2yo winners Not Bad For A Boy (7f AW; RPR 78) & King Dragon (6f; 89) and Italian winners Very Glamour (6f-1m) & Canarina (5f-6f inc at 2); dam best run 1m on 2yo debut (61) half-sister to US 1m Grade 3 winner Media Mogul

racingFormOutcome.overview: 36,000euros foal, 42,000gns yearling; half-sister to several winners out of a sister to St Leger winner Rule Of Law; likely she'll need to be smart to win this on debut and yard only 3-105 with 2yos in recent seasons.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: French 2,000 Gns/Derby winner, also high-class at 2, well related; excellent young sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E36,000 F, 42,000gns Y; 8th foal; half-sister to winners Levanto (1m-1m4f inc AW 2yo; RPR 102), Paleo (7f GB 2yo/6f US; 82), Super Nancy (Italian 6f-1m) and Bonia De Mas (Italian 1m1f-1m2f); dam placed 6f at 2 (82), half-sister to Leger winner Rule Of Law

racingFormOutcome.overview: First foal of an AW winner in France; likely she has a future but this a stiff introduction.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: 9f winner at 2, won Derby at 3, brilliant family of  Lammtarra; sired late-season 2yos in first crop
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam French 7.5f AW winner (RPR 81), sister to 1m-1m6f GB/UAE winner Achill Bay, half-sister to 11.3f Listed winner Hammiya out of 7.5f 2yo Listed winnng half-sister to 5f Group 3 winner/French 1,000 second Pont-Aven

racingFormOutcome.overview: Pleasing start to her career when second in 7f maiden here three weeks ago, keeping on well in the closing stages; extra furlong will help and open to improvement.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: 6f winner at 2, later top-class sprinter, winner of July Cup; moved to Italy 2015
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First living foal; dam 1m3f-1m4f winner (inc AW; RPR 93), out of French 10.5f Group 3 winning half-sister to useful 1m2f-2m Flat/2m-2m6f hurdle winner Mirjan out of Lusted-placed 1m4f winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: 45,000euros yearling; half-sister to three winners out of a winner in France; yard's newcomers usually better for their initial experience.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: excelled over 6f-1m at 2-3, won Phoenix S, & Irish 2,000 Gns; very good sire, inc The Grey Gatsby
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E45,000 Y; 6th foal; half-sister to winners Lord George (8.6f-11.4f inc at 2/AW; RPR 98), Persiste Et Signe (Listed-placed 1m-9.5f AW; 101) & Tres Honore (7.5f AW; 80/2m1f jumps); dam French 6f-1m 2yo winner, half-sister to useful 7f/7.5f winner Macellya

racingFormOutcome.overview: 400,000gns yearling; half-sister to seven winners, notably high-class Tante Rose (RPR 120); one of two newcomers for yard who won both divisions of this maiden last year.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 6f 2yo and 6f-1m 3yo in Aus; champion Aus sire, returns to Europe 2014
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 400,000gns Y; 11th foal; half-sister to 7 winners inc Tante Rose (6f-7f inc Group 1; RPR 120), Melodramatic (1m; 102), Bold Lass (7f-1m inc at 2; 102) and Rosie's Posy (5.7f 2yo 71; dam of Make Believe) dam 5f-7f winner (inc at 2/Listed; 108)

racingFormOutcome.overview: 20-1, green and down the field in 7f maiden here three weeks ago (behind Golden Nectar); likely a longer-term prospect.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 6-8f colt on dirt/turf in US, a leading US sire, can get top-class 2yos; progeny progress
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Ninth foal; half-sister to seven winners inc Ikhtisas (1m2f; RPR 81) and 7f-8.5f winners Distorted Love (USA) and Not A Given (US/UAE); dam Argentinian 1m Gr 1 winner (also US Graded stakes placed at 6.5f)

racingFormOutcome.overview: Showed something to work on despite finishing ninth of 13 on her debut here six weeks ago; should be more clued up this time and although she needs a big step forward, it could be forthcoming.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unraced at 2, later top class over 8-10f, high-class sire inc. Dutch Art & Nannina
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: (29,000gns vendor F); 5th iving foal; half-sister to winners Saloomy (6f inc AW; RPR 91), Tides Reach (7f-1m inc at 2/AW; 82) & Shahaama (6f; 69); dam 5.7f winner (65), sister to 5f Gr 1 (Abbaye) winner Avonbridge, half-sister to Abbaye winner Patavellian

racingFormOutcome.overview: First foal of a maiden from the family of very smart Ertijaal; represents powerful stable and market confidence behind her would look significant.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class sprinter, excellent sire, can get fast, high-class 2yos, progeny often progress well
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam unplaced 7f-1m1f (RPR 44), closely related to 1m Listed winner Shabiba (dam of very smart 5f-7f winner Ertijaal), half-sister to Group-placed 6f 2yo AW winner Darajaat out of 7f Group 3 winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Strong in the market ahead of her Nottingham debut three weeks ago and travelled strongly before finishing third (1m, good to soft); winner there has since run well in Listed company and she looks a major player with improvement likely; tongue-tied for the first time.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart 12f colt at 3-4 in Fr, later G1 winner in US/Canada, brother to Dansili; good young sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 6th foal; sister to 1m2f AW winner Good Value (87), half-brother to Singapore 7f winner Digress; dam placed 1m2f (63), closely related to Group 2/3 winner around 1m2f Weightless, half-sister to 7f Gr 3 winner Main Aim out of 1m Gr 3 winner

racingFormOutcome.owner: Ann Black,M Al Qatami & K M Al Mudhaf
racingFormOutcome.overview: 30,000euros foal, 40,000gns yearling; half-sister to four winners, including two Pattern-race winners, and plenty of appeal on paper; betting usually a good guide to the expectations of the stable's newcomers.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unbeaten 2yo inc. top renewal of Prix Morny, family of Gilt Edge Girl; moved to Italy 2016
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E30m,000 F, 40,000gns Y; 10th foal; half-sister to four winners inc Tropical Paradise (6f-7f inc at 2/Gr 3; RPR 111), Harlem Shake (Italian 5f Gr 3; 105) and Nicomedia (8.6f/1m2f AW; 75); dam 6f 2yo winner (80), out of French 1m3f/1m4f winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Showed plenty to work on when fourth behind facile winner on soft ground at Nottingham three weeks ago; sounder surface should help and no surprise to see her in the shake up.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: won Prix du Jockey-Club & Prix Jean Prat; excellent source of 2yos summer onwards, Classic sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 450,000gns Y; sixth foal; half-sister to winners Silk Sari (1m4f-14.6f; inc Group 2; RPR 112), Dreamlike (1m AW 2yo; 88) and Fashion Fund (US 1m-1m1f); dam unraced half-sister to Racing Post Trophy winner Ibn Khaldun out of Irish 1,000 winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Made an encouraging start to her career when fourth at Newbury 11 days ago and open to improvement; pedigree does suggest it will be over middle distances next season though.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: Australian champion sprinter, champion sire in Australia; sire of Fascinating Rock and Qualify
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Third foal; closely related to 1m2f winner Istanbul Bey (RPR 95), half-sister to 1m5f-2m5f winner Star Rider (103); dam 1m4f AW winner/Park Hill second (106), half-sister to 1m2f 2yo Listed winner Under The Rainbow out of 1m4f Listed winner
